From: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
Date: Tue, 12 Mar 2024 00:17:46 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] AOSCOS: fix(iris_bufmgr.c): set PAGE_SIZE as 16384 on
 LoongArch (LP64)

16KiB is the most commonly found kernel page size on LoongArch
platforms. Limit this to LP64 platforms for now, as this is the only
one that we support.

Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 src/gallium/drivers/iris/iris_bufmgr.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/gallium/drivers/iris/iris_bufmgr.c b/src/gallium/drivers/iris/iris_bufmgr.c
index ed8d0848279..9ec01965f0b 100644
--- a/src/gallium/drivers/iris/iris_bufmgr.c
+++ b/src/gallium/drivers/iris/iris_bufmgr.c
@@ -96,8 +96,16 @@
  * included here.
  */
 #ifndef PAGE_SIZE
+/* 16KiB is the most commonly found kernel page size on LoongArch
+ * platforms. Limit this to LP64 platforms for now, as this is the only
+ * one that we support.
+ */
+#if defined(__loongarch_lp64)
+#define PAGE_SIZE 16384
+#else
 #define PAGE_SIZE 4096
 #endif
+#endif
 
